data.title: Buying match programmes (soccer and Gaelic games)
data.meta_description: Hi all, Looking to buy the following programmes if anyone has any of them at all! The replayed FAI Cup Final in 1971. Limerick v Drogheda
data.text:
Hi all,

Looking to buy the following programmes if anyone has any of them at all!

The replayed FAI Cup Final in 1971. Limerick v Drogheda

The League of Ireland Final matches in the 1959–60 (Dundalk as no other programme) and 1979–80 seasons (teamsheet away to Athlone)

The 1992 (Kilkenny in Limerick) and 2012 (Longford away) 1st Division League of Ireland concluding matches for Limerick.

League of Ireland Shield -1953-1954 (first game away to Dundalk or the Final)

Munster Senior Cup Finals - 1937–38 (Cork), 1948–49 (Waterford), 1953–54 (Albert Rovers), 1962–63 (Cork Hibernians), 1976–77 (Cork Celtic, 1984-1985 (Cobh), 1988–89 (Cork), 1994–95 + 2011–12 (Cork)

Dublin City Cup - 1959 (Drumcondra) and 1970 (Waterford)

World Cup 1994 (Lithuania away qualifier)

Fairview Rangers: FAI Junior Cup Finals: 2020, 2010, 2004, 2003, 2002, 1999, 1998, 1997 and 1965

Amateur/Junior Ireland programmes from the late 90s/early 00s

All-Ireland programmes

Senior hurling: 1897, 1918, 1921, 1934, 1936, 1940

1935, 1941, 1954 - Junior Hurling

1940 - Minor hurling

1940s/1950s - Limerick (Thomas O'Brien: Ahane)

2014 and 2007: All-Ireland Intermediate Championship – Jack McGrath Cup: Camogie

1977 - Junior Camogie

1988 County Junior Camogie Final: Ballybrown

1989: Ballybrown v Roanmore Munster Hurling Championship

2012: Limerick Junior Camogie County and Munster Finals (club: Ballybrown)

2017: Limerick Junior B football county final

Interfirm- Shannon Aerospace (Lufthansa) 1990, Wang (Limerick) - 1982, 1984, 1987, 1988, 1989

Limerick All-Ireland handball

2013: Nicky Rackard - Donegal

Thanks! I've been collecting for a few years and these are all programmes of personal, local interest. Any help would be greatly appreciated.
